        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 2:52PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 252 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
White Plains, or near Dobson, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Airy...
Flat Rock...
Dobson...
Pilot Mountain...
Pine Ridge...
Pilot Mountain State Park...
and Toast.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
